---
pageable: true
per_page: 10
---

.container
  .row
    .twelve.columns
      %h4.c_pseudo-icon.c_pseudo-icon--happy Hey there
      %p
        I'm
        %a{href: "https://twitter.com/fredrivett"} Fred
        and I like to&nbsp;
        %a{href: "https://www.producthunt.com/@fredrivett/made"}> make stuff
        \.
        I&nbsp;
        %a{href: "https://wearecontrast.com"}> design
        ,
        %a{href: "https://github.com/fredrivett"} code
        and&nbsp;
        %a{href: "https://medium.com/fredrivett"}> write
        \.
      %p
        Front End Dev&nbsp;
        %a{href: "https://store.tpo.com"}> @TPO
        , 1/2&nbsp;
        %a{href: "https://wearecontrast.com"}> @wecontrast
        \.
      %p
        %small
          %a{href: "https://medium.com/@fredrivett/fumbling-forwards-5716c52e090#.9eo80twy9"}
            p.s. I don't know what I'm doing.
  .row
    .ten.columns.centered
      .o_spacer.o_spacer--large
        - if paginate && num_pages > 1
          %p
            Page #{page_number} of #{num_pages}
          - if prev_page
            %p= link_to 'Previous page', prev_page
        #section
          %ol.o_naked-list
            %li
              %h2.c_article-list-head.c_pseudo-icon.c_pseudo-icon--arrow
                Latest
            - page_articles.each_with_index do |article, i|
              %li.c_article-head.c_article-head--list-view
                %h3.c_article-head__title= link_to article.title, article
                %time.c_article-head__date{datetime: article.date.strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%l:%M:%S%z')}= article.date.strftime('%b %e')
                / use article.summary(250) if you have Nokogiri available to show just the first 250 characters
                / = article.body
        - if paginate
          - if next_page
            %p= link_to 'Next page', next_page
